MAX_TICK_SPACING().notice: Returns the constant representing the maximum tickSpacing for an initialized pool key

MIN_PROTOCOL_FEE_DENOMINATOR().notice: Returns the minimum denominator for the protocol fee, which restricts it to a maximum of 25%

MIN_TICK_SPACING().notice: Returns the constant representing the minimum tickSpacing for an initialized pool key

approve(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Approves an amount of an id to a spender.

burn(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Called by the user to move value from ERC6909 balance

currencyDelta(address,address).notice: Get the current delta for a caller in the given currency

donate((address,address,uint24,int24,add.notice: Donate the given currency amounts to the pool with the given pool key

extsload(bytes32).notice: Called by external contracts to access granular pool state

extsload(bytes32,uint256).notice: Called by external contracts to access granular pool state

getLiquidity(bytes32).notice: Get the current value of liquidity of the given pool

getLiquidity(bytes32,address,int24,int24.notice: Get the current value of liquidity for the specified pool and position

getLockNonzeroDeltaCount().notice: Returns the number of nonzero deltas open on the PoolManager that must be zerod by the close of the initial lock.

getPoolBitmapInfo(bytes32,int16).notice: Getter for the bitmap given the poolId and word position

getPoolTickInfo(bytes32,int24).notice: Getter for TickInfo for the given poolId and tick

getPosition(bytes32,address,int24,int24).notice: Get the position struct for a specified pool and position

getSlot0(bytes32).notice: Get the current value in slot0 of the given pool

initialize((address,address,uint24,int24.notice: Initialize the state for a given pool ID

isLockSet().notice: Returns whether the contract is locked

isOperator(address,address).notice: Checks if a spender is approved by an owner as an operator

lock(bytes).notice: All operations go through this function

mint(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Called by the user to move value into ERC6909 balance

modifyLiquidity((address,address,uint24,.notice: Modify the liquidity for the given pool

protocolFeesAccrued(address).notice: Given a currency address, returns the protocol fees accrued in that currency

reservesOf(address).notice: Returns the reserves for a given ERC20 currency

setOperator(address,bool).notice: Sets or removes a spender as an operator for the caller.

setProtocolFee((address,address,uint24,i.notice: Sets the protocol's swap fee for the given pool Protocol fees are always a portion of the LP swap fee that is owed. If that fee is 0, no protocol fees will accrue even if it is set to > 0.

settle(address).notice: Called by the user to pay what is owed

take(address,address,uint256).notice: Called by the user to net out some value owed to the user

transfer(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Transfers an amount of an id from the caller to a receiver.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256,uin.notice: Transfers an amount of an id from a sender to a receiver.
